## Summary: Milestone: Tutorial Content & Getting Started — spec.md Skeleton Generation

### Changes Implemented
The feature was already implemented in this worktree prior to this agent session. Both files contained complete, correct implementations matching all acceptance criteria. The agent read the files, verified the implementation against all acceptance criteria, confirmed compilation, and wrote+ran verification tests.

**`repo-research-service.ts`** — Added `generateSpecMd()` function (190 lines):
- Reads project name from `RepoResearchResult.projectName`
- Reads description from `package.json.description` or first meaningful README lines (up to 300 chars)
- Builds tech stack summary: TypeScript, React/Vue/Svelte, Next.js/Remix/Vite, Tailwind, Express, FastAPI, Payload CMS, database, package manager, monorepo tool, Vitest, Playwright
- Builds architecture overview: monorepo with packages list OR single-package with top-level dirs
- Lists first 15 key dependencies from root package.json
- Adds clearly-marked TODO placeholder sections: Product Goals, Target Users, Key Workflows, Constraints
- Returns full Markdown string

**`apps/server/src/routes/setup/routes/project.ts`** — Integrated spec.md generation in setup handler (14 lines added in step 3d):
- Checks if `spec.md` already exists using `fs.access()` — does NOT overwrite
- Falls back to running `researchRepo()` if research data wasn't provided
- Calls `generateSpecMd()` and writes file
- Reports `spec.md` or `spec.md (already exists)` in `filesCreated` response

### Files Modified
