### Learnings
- The feature was already fully implemented before this session — the worktree likely had prior work. Always read the files first before writing any code.
- The `generateSpecMd` export is clean: it takes `(projectPath, research)` and returns a `Promise<string>`, making it easily unit-testable.
- The non-overwrite guard uses the standard `try { await fs.access(path) } catch { /* write */ }` pattern consistent with other files in the same route.

### Notes for Developer
- The `generateSpecMd` function reads `package.json` and README independently of the `RepoResearchResult` (which doesn't include raw file content) — this is intentional to get fresh description data.
- Key dependencies shown in `spec.md` come from root `package.json` only (not workspace packages) — this is by design to keep the list focused.
- The architecture section switches automatically between monorepo package listing and single-package top-level directory listing based on `research.monorepo.isMonorepo`.

